u(x,y)
x^{3}\frac{\partial u}{\partial x}-\frac{\partial u}{\partial y}=0
(x,y)
y(x)=\frac{1}{2}(x^{-2}-x_{0}^{-2})
x_{0}\ne 0
\frac{dx}{ds}=x^{3}
\frac{dy}{ds}=-1
\frac{dy}{dx} = -\frac{1}{x^{3}}
\Rightarrow  \int 1 dy = \int -\frac{1}{x^{3}} dx  \Rightarrow y=\frac{1}{2x^{2}}+c
